<p>Consistent use of "None" in flags enumerations indicates that all flag values are cleared. The value 0 should not be used to indicate any other
state, since there is no way to check that the bit <code>0</code> is set.</p>
<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>
<pre>
&lt;Flags()&gt;
Enum FruitType
    Void = 0        ' Non-Compliant
    Banana = 1
    Orange = 2
    Strawberry = 4
End Enum
</pre>
<h2>Compliant Solution</h2>
<pre>
&lt;Flags()&gt;
Enum FruitType
    None = 0        ' Compliant
    Banana = 1
    Orange = 2
    Strawberry = 4
End Enum
</pre>